[div class=p 
	[a href=https://www.yui.ne.jp/np2/ rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Neko Project 2
	]a
	" is an emulator of the Japanese computer system PC-98. It can be used with either 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=libTAS|href=/EmulatorResources/LibTAS)
	" or 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Hourglass|href=/EmulatorResources/Hourglass)
	" to make tool-assisted speedruns.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=Libtas 
	" libTAS
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"libTAS is fully compatible with 
	[a href=https://github.com/TASEmulators/NP2kai rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Neko Project II kai
	]a
	", specifically the SDL build (NOT the "X with GTK2 and SDL" build).
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=WhatYouLlNeed 
	" What you'll need
	$LF
]h4
[ul 
	[li 
		" 
		[a href=https://github.com/clementgallet/libTAS/releases rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"libTAS 1.4.3
		]a
		" or newer.
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				" Remember that the run must sync on an 
				(__wikiLink|displaytext=official emulator version|href=/MovieRules#UseAnOfficialEmulatorVersion)
				" or it will not be accepted.
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[a href=https://github.com/TASEmulators/NP2kai/releases rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"The SDL build of Neko Project II kai
		]a
		".
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				" If that build is insufficient for your needs, 
				[a href=https://github.com/TASEmulators/NP2kai rel=noopener external nofollow 
					"make an issue or a pull request
				]a
				" and we'll try to incorporate your changes.
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
	]li
	[li 
		" Floppy and/or hard drive images for your game.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" A font ROM - this is not strictly necessary for sync, but text will be corrupted or nonexistent if you don't have one. The file 
		[code 
			"font.rom
		]code
		" (md5: 
		[code 
			"38d32748ae49d1815b0614970849fd40
		]code
		") is safe to use.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h4 id=Config 
	" Config 
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"By default, the config file is stored in 
	[code 
		"~/.config/sdlnp21kai/
	]code
	" as 
	[code 
		"np21kai.cfg
	]code
	". 
	[b 
		"You need to create this folder, or else NP2kai will not save the config!
	]b
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" Specify the path to the font ROM on the line 
		[code 
			"fontfile = 
		]code
		", otherwise some characters will not show up properly. Use whichever one you like, this does not affect sync.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" Specify the hard drive on the line 
		[code 
			"HDD1FILE = 
		]code
		".
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" If you want to set up rhythm files (
		[code 
			"2608_BD.WAV
		]code
		", etc), put them in 
		[code 
			"~/.config/sdlnp21kai/
		]code
		". 
		[b 
			"These files have to be in all uppercase, including the file extension!
		]b
		" Otherwise NP2kai will not be able to find them.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"If you want to adjust any system settings such as the CPU speed and the memory, run 
	[code 
		"sdlnp21kai
	]code
	" natively and middle-click the window to open the built-in GUI (never open this menu in your submission movie). Note any changes from the default settings in your submission notes or in the movie annotations. We may ask for the contents of your 
	[code 
		"np21kai.cfg
	]code
	" file if we have trouble syncing your movie.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=UsingWithLibtas 
	" Using with libTAS
	$LF
]h4
[ul 
	[li 
		" The executable path should be set to 
		[code 
			"/usr/bin/sdlnp21kai
		]code
		", or wherever you've installed it.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" Make sure 
		[code 
			"Runtime -> Time tracking -> SDL_GetTicks()
		]code
		" is checked.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" If you want to start with a floppy in the drive, put its path in Command-line options.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" Set 
		[code 
			"Frames per second
		]code
		" to 1000000000 / 17723226
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h4 id=MovieSubmissions 
	" Movie submissions
	$LF
]h4
[ul 
	[li 
		" Follow all rules already in place for 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=submitting libTAS movies|href=/EmulatorResources/LibTAS#MovieSubmissions)
		".
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" 
		[b 
			"Make sure your floppies and hard drives are brand new!
		]b
		" Having different files on the drive images may cause desyncs when run on other systems. User data such as saves and high scores are written directly to the drive images, so always start your movie with fresh, untouched floppy drives/hard drives.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" When making a libTAS movie that you plan to submit to TASVideos or upload it to userfiles, put 
		[code 
			"Platform: PC98
		]code
		" at the very start of the movie annotations, that way the site will recognize your platform properly.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" 
		[b 
			"Never open the built-in GUI during your movie!
		]b
		" Any configuration changes should be made outside of libTAS.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" In your description or movie annotations, please provide the following:
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				" libTAS version
				$LF
			]li
			[li 
				" MD5 hashes of any hard drive files and/or floppy files you used
				$LF
			]li
			[li 
				" Any changes you made to your configuration. Posting your entire 
				[code 
					"np21kai.cfg
				]code
				" file is ideal.
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
	]li
]ul
